{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πρόθυρ-ον</b>, τό, <br /> <b>front-door, door-way,</b> especially of the entrance to the αὐλή, ἐκ δ᾽ ἔλασε προθύροιο καὶ αἰθούσης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.323, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 3.493: _plural_, στῆ δ᾽.. ἐπὶ προθύροις Ὀδυσῆος, οὐδοῦ ἐπ᾽ αὐλείου 1.103; πρόθυρα δωμάτων 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 966 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Troades” 194 (Lyric poetry) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of the entrance to the μέγαρον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.10, 101, 386, 21.299. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>porch, portico,</b> παραστάδας καὶ π. βούλει ποικίλα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 42, compare 4th c.BC: Dicaearchus Geographus Hist. 59.8. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>space before a door,</b> whether or not it is a <b>porch</b> or <b>portico</b>: before the outmost entrance, <i>plural</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.20, 10.220, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.140, 6.35; _sing._, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 314c, “Smp.” 175a: Ἑρμαῖ.. λίθινοι.. ἐν ἰδίοις προθύροις 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.27, compare 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.78 (_sing._), 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 802 (_plural_), 875 (_sing._), 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Epigrammata” 26 (_sing._): before the entrance to the μέγαρον, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.355 (_sing._)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; before the entrance of a νεωκόριον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.1672.208. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, Κόρινθος Ἰσθμίου πρόθυρον Ποτειδᾶνος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 13.5; ἐπὶ τοῖς τοῦ ἀ